OL,3,CWhy Starmer picked Mandelson for
OL,4,CWashington
OL,6,FThat mission to America represents
OL,7,Fquite an extension of the typical
OL,8,Ffunctions of Downing Street chiefs of
OL,9,Fstaff, who are political appointees (I
OL,10,Fcan't even remember Cummings ever
OL,11,Fhaving quite that responsibility).
OL,13,FThe point is that Mandelson was always
OL,14,FMcSweeney's choice.
OL,16,FOthers were in the frame for the plum
OL,17,Fambassadorship, including Richard
OL,18,FMoore, chief of Mi6, the famous "C".
